</div> </div>
<figcaption id=primary-image__figcap_1-0 class="comp primary-image__figcap mntl-figure-caption figure-article-caption"> <span class=figure-article-caption-text>Kelly Slater Sunscreen Line "Lovely Lisa".</span>
<span class=figure-article-caption-owner>Credit : <p>Lovely Lisa</p></span>
</figcaption></figure>
<div id=article-content_1-0 class="comp article-content mntl-block"><div id=mntl-sc-page_1-0 class="comp mntl-sc-page mntl-block structured-content" data-sc-sticky-offset=90 data-sc-ad-label-height=24 data-sc-ad-track-spacing=100 data-sc-min-track-height=250 data-sc-max-track-height=600 data-sc-breakpoint=50em data-sc-load-immediate=4 data-sc-content-positions="[1, 1250, 1550, 1950, 2350, 2750, 3150, 3550, 3950]" data-bind-scroll-on-start=true><p id=mntl-sc-block_1-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> <a href=https://people.com/kelly-slater-hints-surfing-career-coming-to-end-8634680 data-component=link data-source=inlineLink data-type=internalLink data-ordinal=1>Kelly Slater</a> is hopping on the skincare wave.
</p>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_2-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
<p id=mntl-sc-block_3-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> The 11-time world champion surfer spoke with PEOLPE exclusively about the launch of <a href=https://freaksofnature.com/password data-component=link data-source=inlineLink data-type=externalLink data-ordinal=1 rel="nofollow noopener" target=_blank>Lucky Lisa</a>, his new skincare brand inspired by his active lifestyle — and hours spent under the sun.
</p>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_4-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
<p id=mntl-sc-block_5-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> "I was looking for a good SPF that would last a long time [but] I'm really particular about what I use," Slater, 52, tells PEOPLE exclusively of how the brand came to be. It consists of three products: the Deeper Dive Moisturizer, the Daily Defender Sunscreen and the Peak Performance Sunscreen.
</p>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_6-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
<p id=mntl-sc-block_7-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> The professional surfer says he's in the water "all day long," so creating a product that he could "trust" would protect his skin from the sun's strong rays was at the forefront of this concept.
</p>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_8-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
<p id=mntl-sc-block_9-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> Slater's commitment to skin protection wasn't always a priority for the Florida native who grew up with Cocoa Beach in his backyard. The surfing pro admits he "didn't worry about it" in his younger years, despite "getting killed by the sun" while outside.
</p>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_10-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_11-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block people-sc-block-featuredlink mntl-sc-block-universal-featured-link mntl-sc-block-universal-featured-link--related"><a href=https://people.com/kelly-slater-hints-surfing-career-coming-to-end-8634680 rel=nocaes id=mntl-sc-block-universal-featured-link__link_1-0 class="mntl-sc-block-universal-featured-link__link mntl-text-link text-utility-300 global-link" data-tracking-container=true data-tracking-id=featured-link><span class=link__wrapper>Kelly Slater Gets Emotional as He Hints His Decades-Long Surfing Career Is Coming to an End</span></a>
</div>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_12-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
<figure id=mntl-sc-block_13-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block people-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block-image--no-theme no-theme figure-landscape figure-high-res"> <div class=figure-media>
<div class=img-placeholder style=padding-bottom:66.6%>
<img data-src="https://people.com/thmb/9EuSdJzHGdZlfXcg7LZQQ6F-VbU=/4000x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(749x0:751x2)/kelly-slater-sunscreen-050224-1-2782700d67f444ccabb08979b36db3fc.jpg" width=1500 height=1000 data-srcset="https://people.com/thmb/9EuSdJzHGdZlfXcg7LZQQ6F-VbU=/4000x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(749x0:751x2)/kelly-slater-sunscreen-050224-1-2782700d67f444ccabb08979b36db3fc.jpg 4000w" data-sizes=4000px class="mntl-image universal-image__image lazyloadwait lazyloaded" data-expand=300 id=mntl-sc-block-image_1-0 data-click-tracked=true data-img-lightbox-variant data-tracking-container=true data-img-lightbox=true sizes srcset src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Kelly Slater Sunscreen 'Lovely Lisa'">
</div> </div>
<figcaption id=mntl-figure-caption_1-0 class="comp mntl-figure-caption text-utility-100 figure-article-caption"> <span class=figure-article-caption-text>11-time world champion surfer Kelly Slater launches sunscreen line, Lovely Lisa.</span>
<span class=figure-article-caption-owner><p>Lovely Lisa</p></span>
</figcaption></figure>
<p id=mntl-sc-block_14-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> "I remember a couple of times as a kid just going all day in the water and not using sunscreen and then paying the price the next day," Slater recalls. "I'd put sunglasses on, a towel over my head and lather up with everything I could because I was so fried the next day — and then, my whole body would peel."
</p>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_15-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
<p id=mntl-sc-block_16-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> The pro athlete, who's surfed all over the world throughout his decades-long career, rattled off a few of the most beautiful places he's traveled for the sport. Not only did he leave with incredible memories, but also some painful sunburns that he remembers to this day.
</p>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_17-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
<p id=mntl-sc-block_18-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> "One time I was in Fiji in my twenties and the waves were so good, I just didn't put anything on," Slater recalls before he returned to his home at the time. "For three days, I didn't leave the house. I got back from the trip and I just peeled. I was in pain for the rest of the week."
</p>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_19-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_20-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block people-sc-block-featuredlink mntl-sc-block-universal-featured-link mntl-sc-block-universal-featured-link--related"><a href=https://people.com/surfer-john-john-florence-kelly-slater-rematch-would-be-incredible-exclusive-7643085 rel=nocaes id=mntl-sc-block-universal-featured-link__link_2-0 class="mntl-sc-block-universal-featured-link__link mntl-text-link text-utility-300 global-link" data-tracking-container=true data-tracking-id=featured-link><span class=link__wrapper>Surfer John John Florence Says a Kelly Slater Rematch ‘Would Be Incredible’ a Decade After the ‘Greatest Heat’</span></a>
</div>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_21-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
<p id=mntl-sc-block_22-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> As a surfer who's regarded as "the greatest of all time" in the sport, Slater explains the reason why he used to skip the sunscreen step: "You forget everything else that exists when the waves are good."
</p>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_23-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
<p id=mntl-sc-block_24-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> However, Slater says he's "learned the hard way" thanks to those past painful experiences. "I've been in the sun for probably hundreds of thousands of hours or more. It's kind of amazing I still have skin after all this time."<br>
</p>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_25-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
<figure id=mntl-sc-block_26-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block people-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block-image--no-theme no-theme figure-landscape figure-high-res"> <div class=figure-media>
<div class=img-placeholder style=padding-bottom:66.6%>
<img data-src="https://people.com/thmb/y_sUU_5ok6yMxLiFSWmJ0_kzvtg=/4000x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(722x197:724x199)/kelly-slater-margaret-river-pro-surfing-competition-041724-5-f10319e1b0d5474ab200a1dd3ddba54b.jpg" width=1500 height=1000 data-srcset="https://people.com/thmb/y_sUU_5ok6yMxLiFSWmJ0_kzvtg=/4000x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(722x197:724x199)/kelly-slater-margaret-river-pro-surfing-competition-041724-5-f10319e1b0d5474ab200a1dd3ddba54b.jpg 4000w" data-sizes=4000px alt="Eleven-time WSL Champion Kelly Slater of the United States after surfing in Heat 5 of the Round of 32 at the Western Australia Margaret River Pro" class="mntl-image universal-image__image lazyloadwait lazyloaded" data-expand=300 id=mntl-sc-block-image_2-0 data-click-tracked=true data-img-lightbox-variant data-tracking-container=true data-img-lightbox=true sizes srcset src="data:image/jpeg;base64,">
</div> </div>
<figcaption id=mntl-figure-caption_2-0 class="comp mntl-figure-caption text-utility-100 figure-article-caption"> <span class=figure-article-caption-text>Kelly Slater after surfing at the Wester Australia Margaret River Pro on April 16, 2024.</span>
<span class=figure-article-caption-owner><p>Beatriz Ryder/World Surf League via Getty Images</p></span>
</figcaption></figure>
<p id=mntl-sc-block_27-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> "So now as I'm aging, I take more time to take care of myself," assures Slater, who turns to his Lovely Lisa collection for an assist. "I like to have a hand in the knowledge behind the products I use or the things I do."
</p>
<div id=mntl-sc-block_28-0 class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block sf-hidden"></div>
